"A high level delegation from Djibouti led by President Ismail Guelleh landed at Mogadishu's Adan Abdulle International Airport to attend the inauguration ceremony of President Hassan Sheikh Mohamud," state-owned SNTV said in a tweet and shared pictures of Guelleh and his delegation. The State televiosn also tweeted pictures of Ethiopian Prime Minister Abiy Ahmed arriving in Mogadishu for the ceremony. Kenyan President Uhuru Kenyatta was also received at the Mogadishu airport by the Somali Prime Minister Mohamed Hussein Roble. Security has been beefed up in the capital and the city put under curfew ahead of the inauguration. Earlier on Thursday reports said mortar rounds were fired in Mogadishu mainly hitting civilian homes.
Sheikh Mohamud.was sworn in on May 15 immediately after he was elected by the country's bicameral parliament. His predecessor handed over power on May 23.
--BBC--